SIMPLE: bushhammer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bushhammer
<hw>Bush"ham`mer</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hammer with a
head formed of a bundle of square bars, with pyramidal points, arranged
in rows, or a solid head with a face cut into a number of rows of such
points; -- used for dressing stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushhammer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bushhammer
<hw>Bush"ham`mer</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To dress with bushhammer;
<as>as, to <ex>bushhammer</ex> a block of granite</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushido</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
